                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/383.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-02T13:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American Consul General at Guayaquil telegraphed this morning that our
                    consular agent at Esmeraldas reports that that city is practically besieged by
                    the revolutionists and that the situation is becoming difficult.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
